Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Stackpole","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Welsh: habitational name from Stackpole (Pembrokeshire), apparently named with Old Norse <i>stakkr</i> ‘stack’ + <i>pollr</i> ‘pool’, referring to a stack of rocks on the coast at the entrance to Broadhaven. The name was taken to Ireland and adapted by settlers of Norman descent, where it is recorded in Dublin as early as 1200. The name has been Gaelicized as <b>de Stacapúl</b>; the family was also known in Irish as <b>Galldubh</b> ‘dark stranger’."],"variants":[{"name":"Stackpoole","meanings":["English (Cheshire) and Welsh: variant of   Stackpole  ."]}]},{"name":"Philip","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Philip de Stackpole II was born in 1230, in Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the son of Philip de Stackpole I. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1298, in Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1230–1298":"1230–1298","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1230–1298":"1230–1298","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1230–1298":"1230–1298","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Philip de Stackpole II est né en 1230, à Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, fils de Philip de Stackpole I. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1298, à Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Galles, à l’âge de 68 ans."},"de":{"1230–1298":"1230–1298","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales","lifeSummary":"Philip de Stackpole II wurde 1230 in Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom, als Sohn von Philip de Stackpole I geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1298 im Alter von 68 Jahren in Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales."},"ht":{"1230–1298":"1230–1298","1250–Male":"1250–Desede","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"hu":{"1230–1298":"1230–1298","1250–Male":"1250–elhunyt","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Stackpole, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"id":{"1230–1298":"1230–1298","1250–Male":"1250–Telah Meninggal","1210–1280":"1210–1280","1298":"1298","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","12